claim.claim-text:
1. A receiver, comprising:
a first filter including at least a low pass filter, the low pass filter having:
a transistor having first, second, and third terminals;
a first capacitor coupled between the second terminal and a ground; and
a second capacitor coupled between the first terminal and the second terminal;

a current source configured to receive filtered current from the first filter and relay the filtered current to a second filter;
the second filter configured to filter the filtered current from the current source; and
a current mirror configured to receive the filtered current from the second filter and provide a current signal corresponding to the filtered current.

13. A method of processing a signal received by a receiver, the method comprising:
receiving a filtered current by a current source from a first filter including at least a low pass filter, the low pass filter having:
a transistor including first, second, and third terminals;
a first capacitor coupled between the second terminal and a ground; and
a second capacitor coupled between the first terminal and the second terminal;

relaying the filtered current to a second filter;
filtering the relayed current by the second filter from the current source; and
receiving the filtered current by a current mirror from the second filter to provide a current signal corresponding to the filtered current.
